  %section.section--white.soft--ends
    .row
      .large-4.columns.large-offset-2
        =image_tag "supplies.gif"
      .large-4.columns.end
        %h2 Supplies
        %ul
          %li Two Pieces of Paper
          %li Scissors or Exacto
          %li Pen Cap
          %li Rubber Cement
        %a.button--small{href: "/Chomp--Black.pdf"} Download Chomp Pattern

    %hr

    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h2 Step 1
    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Download the PDF
        %p This contains an overview page, the top of the Chomp, and the bottom of the Chomp. <a href="/Chomp--Black.pdf">Download it here</a>
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Print out pages
        %p Print the top and bottom onto cardstock. The thicker paper helps with the durability of the toy.

    %hr

    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h2 Step 2
    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Cut out the Chomps
        %p Carefully cut around the outside of the Chomp pattern.
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Scour all dashed lines
        %p Gently score along the dashed lines. This helps to create crisper folds. You should now be able to fold these easily.
    %hr
    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h2 Step 3
    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Glue tabs A-F
        %p Put glue on Tab A. Glue side A to Tab A. Hold until bond has formed. Repeat for tabs B, C, D, E, and F.
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Repeat for B-F
        %p Repeat glue for tabs B, C, D, E, and F. Don’t do G and H yet!

    %hr
    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h2 Step 4
    .row
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Assemble pieces
        %p Take the finished head and slide it into the unglued side of the bottom. Be sure the colors of the teeth match up.
      .large-4.columns
        %h4 Glue tabs G and H
        %p Repeat first steps on tabs G and H. This is the trickiest part, as there is little room between the top and the sides.

